<br>
If you are playing a wizard, this is an important document, which you need to read.  This document will tell you, in cold hard numbers, how weak your class is.  This is not a flame.  This is a warning, letting you know what is in store for you.  I have a 54th level wizard, and have wasted a year of my life into a class that in ineffective.<br>
<br>
Like you, when I started playing my wizard, this is what I was told.  (Taken directly from the Everquest Web Site)<br>
Certainly, other magic users are proficient in their own areas, but the wizard is most effective in battle. That is, as long as they have someone very sturdy to protect them from melee attacks. What wizard’s gain in magical attack ability, they lose in defensive capability.<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/guidebook/classes.jsp">everquest.station.sony.co...lasses.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
You are given dreams that you will be a master of damage, with huge amounts of power at your fingertips.  You will have to be careful with this damage, as you will be able to make a mob realize just how dangerous you are and come and crush your frail form.  You have visions that people will seek you out for your ability to add value to a group.<br>
<br>
In reality, this is not the case.  Your damage is sadly lacking compared to other classes, and will find that you are a drawback to your comrades.  Instead of people loving you, and wanting you in there groups, they will shun you and not want you in their group as you will just take one sixth of their hard earned experience.<br>
With you in their groups, they will not be able to kill the same mobs, as they will not have a solid enough of a group.  Every group you are in will be described as “Not the Right Group”<br>
<br>
If you are playing a wizard, do yourself a favor and make a new character!  Show Verant that you do not like the class, and you want them to do something about it.    Boycott the class!<br>
<br>
First of all, let us look and compare a wizard to a monk.  I use this example because I often play with a friend of mine who is a rogue, and it is the easiest to judge his gear.  We are both level 54.  First we shall describe myself.  <br>
<br>
=============================================<br>
The Wizard :<br>
My wizard has an int of 200 and has a mana of 2518.  I have focused on mana gear and have a total of 250 mana from extra mana from just gear.  This is invaluable when playing as it gives me a deeper pool with which to use.  This number is extracted from eq.castersrealm.com using their mana calculator.<br>
<br>
My main spell is draught of fire.  This is because it has a low casting time, does a good amount of damage with a good ratio (215mana/644dmg).  <br>
With my mana pool I can cast this spell a total of 11 times before I have run out of mana.<br>
<br>
This is a total of 7084 points of damage assuming that you get a total of 0 resists from the mob.  <br>
<br>
This is a reasonable amount of damage, and when you look at it, the amount is actually quite nice, and you honestly believe that you have done your fair share of damage.  <br>
An enchanter with clarity, in addition to harvest means that you can get that bar back in a total of 8 minutes.<br>
<br>
This gives you a total of 885 points of damage per minute on average you have added to the combat.  This is the most efficient you will ever be, as Verant has described you as most efficient in battle.<br>
<br>
The Rogue :<br>
My good friend plays a rogue.  He has roughly a 150 strength.  He uses a ragebringer as his primary weapon (as his epic was very easy to complete compared to mine) and he uses a Trakasaur's Tooth as his primary weapon.  <br>
Now I used Copelands weapon analyzer to give the total damage he can do each minute.  This will also assume that the rogue has had the same enchanter who gave me the clarity give him an Aanya's Quickening which gives him a 64 percent haste bonus above his normal. <br>
This is a total of 5658 points of damage each minute.<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/copelandeq/weaponanalyzer.html">www.geocities.com/copelan...lyzer.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The Summary :<br>
So, as it turns out, the one rogue does more damage than 6 copies of me in a fight.  This amount is increased even more when you remember that a rogue does not have to worry about resists.<br>
<br>
So, please, until Verant realizes their mistake, shelve your wizard and start a different class.  Your one part where you are supposed to shine has been taken away, and if you are going to play the game, play a class that will matter.<br>
