<br>
I would be interested to see a rogue take on Enemy_01 and a wizard take on Enemy_01.  Depending on the toughness of the mob, the rogue will probably take some substantial damage from the fight.  Rogue hitpoint regeneration will come nowhere near a wizards mana regeneration.<br>
<br>
For instance, let's assume I take an unbuffed, unsowed 50 wizard to Rathe Mountains with an unbuffed, unsowed 50 rogue.  The wizard takes a giant down in say, 1 minute.  The wizard would then have say 8 minutes of med time ahead of him.  The wizard's rogue pal takes the giant down but would probably take some pretty good damage out of the fight.  Now he gets to sit as well.  You absolutely cannot tell me he will regenerate his hitpoints in 8 minutes.  <br>
<br>
